Grassroots UBI

	Philosophy

		-
			A grassroots UBI, or GrUBI, is a universal basic income program operated by private
			citizens or organizations independently of the government, which is funded through
			voluntary donations.
		-

	Principles

		Fund

			-
				The fund of an GrUBI is the set of accounts in which the money with which it funds
				its payments is stored.
			-

		Subscribers

			-
				A recipient of a GrUBI is referred to as a subscriber.
			-